  "prompt": "If a person weighs 150 pounds, how much should their arm weigh?",
  "response": "The weight of an individual's arm can be estimated using general body composition percentages. On average, an arm constitutes about 5-6% of a person's total body weight. For a person weighing 150 pounds, the weight of one arm would typically be around:\n\n\\(150 \\text{ pounds} \\times 0.05 = 7.5 \\text{ pounds}\\) \n\nto \n\n\\(150 \\text{ pounds} \\times 0.06 = 9.0 \\text{ pounds}\\). \n\nSo, an arm might weigh approximately 7.5 to 9 pounds. Keep in mind that this is a rough estimate, and individual variations in body composition can cause these numbers to vary.",
